column32:
​Think of this ladder as representing where people stand in the United States. At the top of the ladder are the people who are the best off - those who have the most money, the most education, and the most respected jobs. At the bottom are the people who are the worst off - who have the least money, least education, and the least respected jobs or no job.  The higher up you are on this ladder, the closer you are to the people at the very top; the lower you are, the closer you are to the people at the very bottom. 







Please indicate the rung where you think you stand at this time in your life, RELATIVE TO OTHER PEOPLE IN THE UNITED STATES. (1-10)

Example 1: I had the experience [[Field-1]] because of [A, B, C...]

Example 2: I would not have had the experience [[Field-1]], if I had never experienced [A, B, C...]

 

Note: The memory for the current evaluation will appear as an option below. Please ignore, as self-selecting the memory as relating to itself is redundant.

 

Below is a reminder of the details:



For each target life experience, select the life experiences from those that you previously listed that caused the target life experience to occur. When considering whether a life experience caused a target life experience, consider whether the target life experience would exist if not for the other life experience. For example, person X may not have had their child if they had not met their future wife, or person Y may not have learned guitar if they had not attended a particular concert.



For each question, you can select as many life experiences as you think that may caused the target life experience or the target life experience depends on.
